# Round 1 Analysis — opc2_uname (2026-06-04/05)

## Emergency Fix: Proxy Routing Reverted

### Problem
Proxy 40001 was routing glm5.1 → `glm5.1_test41003` (1024 variants × KEY1 only = 1024 deployments)
instead of production `glm5.1_uni41001` (256 variants × 7 keys = 1792 deployments).

**Evidence:**
- watchdog log shows: `auth_to_api_40001 上游 http://glm5.1_test41003:4000 连不上 → 502`
- docker-compose.yml had `LITELLM_URL_GLM51: http://glm5.1_test41003:4000/v1/chat/completions`
- Comment in compose: `REVERT INSTRUCTION: 改回 http://glm5.1_uni41001:4000`
- test41003 only has KEY1 → quota exhaustion hits all 1024 deployments simultaneously
- No fallback to other keys → 429 insufficient_quota cascade

### Action
- Changed `LITELLM_URL_GLM51` from test41003 to uni41001
- Changed `LITELLM_MODELS_URL_GLM51` from test41003 to uni41001
- Changed `depends_on` from test41003 to uni41001
- Recreated proxy container: `docker compose up -d --force-recreate auth_to_api_40001`
- Also restarted `dsv4p_uni42001` to clear cooldown state (all 77 deployments were cooldown)

### Verification
- glm5.1 test: HTTP 200, valid response
- dsv4p test: HTTP 200, valid response (after restart to clear cooldown)
- `/health` endpoint shows correct routing: `glm5.1 → glm5.1_uni41001:4000`

