### Key Issues Identified
1. **99.4% traffic goes to glm5.1** — CC settings model is claude-opus-4-8 → mapped to glm5.1 only
2. **429 rate 19.6%** — insufficient_quota errors burning time
3. **429 avg latency 7.1s** — LiteLLM retries 5 times across deployments before giving up
4. **dsv4p barely used (0.4%)** — model routing configuration issue
5. **KEY3-7 dsv4p quota exhausted** (choices=null in non-stream, but works in stream)

## DSv4P Quota Test Results
| Key | Non-Stream | Stream |
|-----|-----------|--------|
| KEY1 | ✅ choices valid | ✅ works |
| KEY2 | ✅ choices valid | ✅ works |
| KEY3 | ❌ choices=null | ✅ works in stream |
| KEY4 | ❌ choices=null | ✅ works in stream |
| KEY5 | ❌ choices=null | ✅ works in stream |
| KEY6 | ❌ choices=null | ✅ works in stream |
| KEY7 | ❌ choices=null | ✅ works in stream |

**Since proxy forces stream=True for all requests, KEY3-7 should work through proxy.**
The 429 error was caused by cooldown state accumulation, not actual quota exhaustion.
After restarting dsv4p_uni42001, all keys work fine through proxy.